  "report_markdown": "# Scouting & strategy report: AJ Dybantsa\n_Question: Analyze the Wizards' path with AJ Dybantsa as their cornerstone._\n\n## Profile  _(from lookup_prospect)_\nBYU, age 19.56, 6'9\", 25.5 pts / 6.8 reb / 3.7 ast.\n\n## Historical comparables  _(from find_comparables)_\n- **James Harden** (2009) \u2014 similarity 72.8, became a superstar (career VORP 87.9); alike on college blocks/game, college eFG%.\n- **James Anderson** (2010) \u2014 similarity 71.2, became a bust (career VORP -0.8); alike on college 3P%, college TS%.\n- **Alec Burks** (2011) \u2014 similarity 70.7, became a starter (career VORP 6.6); alike on college steals/game, college blocks/game.\n- **RJ Barrett** (2019) \u2014 similarity 70.0, became a rotation (career VORP 1.8); alike on college minutes/game, college blocks/game.\n- **T.J. Warren** (2014) \u2014 similarity 68.4, became a starter (career VORP 4.1); alike on college eFG%, college minutes/game.\n\nAcross the analog set the outcomes range widely (all_star, bust, rotation, starter, superstar), which is the basis for the uncertainty below.\n\n## Development projection  _(from project_development)_\n- **P(starter or better): 70%**, P(all-star or better): 50%, P(bust): 11%.\n- Expected career VORP **15.7**, with an honest 80% range of -0.4 to 36.7 (median 9.2).\n- Biggest swing factors: college steals/game (\u2191), age at draft (\u2193), college assists/game (\u2191).\n\n> 80% career-VORP interval spans -0.4 to 36.7 (median 9.2) \u2014 a wide range driven by how differently the comparables developed.\n\n## Roster fit & build path  _(from evaluate_roster_fit)_\n- WAS fit around AJ Dybantsa: **67.0/100**.\n- Biggest unmet needs: **perimeter defense, spacing, rim protection**.\n- Recommended complementary archetypes: 3&D Wing (fills perimeter defense, spacing); Defensive Anchor Big (fills rim protection, perimeter defense); Two-Way Wing (fills perimeter defense, spacing).\n\n## Bottom line\nAJ Dybantsa profiles as a 70%-likely starter-or-better with real star upside (P(all-star+) 50%) but genuine bust risk (11%) \u2014 a wide distribution, not a sure thing. To maximize his value, WAS should prioritize perimeter defense, spacing \u2014 a 3&D Wing is the highest-leverage add.",
